  <div class="mobile-nav-actions">
    <a href="/#kits" class="btn-cart-mobile">Shop Kits ✨</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="page-hero-label">Help</div>
  <h1>Frequently asked <em>questions</em></h1>
  <p class="page-hero-sub">Everything you need to know about our kits, workshops, orders, and returns. Can not find your answer? Email us at hello@creativesolace.com.</p>
</div>

<div class="breadcrumb">
  <a href="/">Home</a> &rsaquo; FAQ
</div>

<div class="faq-wrap">

  <div class="faq-group">
    <h2 class="faq-section-title">About the Kits</h2>

    <details>
      <summary>What comes in the kit?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Every kit includes a premium printed canvas with a 4 cm gallery-wrap border (ready to hang without a frame), all the rhinestones you need to complete the design, an applicator pen, a wax tray, and a tube of B7000 professional adhesive. Everything is included. You do not need to buy anything extra.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Is this the same as diamond painting?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Similar but not the same. Classic diamond painting uses a sticky canvas with a pre-set grid. Our kits use a freestyle approach with B7000 adhesive, so you have more control over where you place each stone. The result looks bolder, more textured, and more like real wall art.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Why B7000 glue and not a sticky canvas?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>B7000 creates a permanent bond. Once the glue cures (24 to 48 hours), the stones are fixed for good. A sticky canvas can lose its grip over time, especially in warm rooms. The precision tip on the B7000 tube also lets you be more deliberate and accurate with your placement.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Do I need to frame it?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>No. The canvas has a 4 cm gallery-wrap border, which means the edges are clean and finished. It looks great hung directly on the wall without a frame.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>How long does it take to complete?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Most people finish in 3 to 6 hours spread over a few sessions. It is a relaxing activity, not a race. Many people do it while watching TV or listening to a podcast.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Is it suitable for beginners?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Yes. That is exactly who it is designed for. If you can hold a pen, you can do this. No creative experience is needed.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>How do I look after the finished piece?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>After the glue has fully cured (24 to 48 hours), the stones are very secure. If the canvas needs cleaning, use a soft dry brush or a lint-free cloth. Do not spray water or cleaning products directly on the surface.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-group">
    <h2 class="faq-section-title">Orders and Shipping</h2>

    <details>
      <summary>How quickly do you ship?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Orders are packed and shipped within 1 to 3 business days of payment. You will receive a confirmation email with a track and trace link once your order is dispatched.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Is shipping free in the Netherlands?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Yes. Shipping is free on all orders within the Netherlands. For orders to Belgium, Germany, or the rest of Europe, shipping costs are calculated at checkout before you pay.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Can I change or cancel my order?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>You have 24 hours from the time of purchase to request a change or cancellation. After that, your order will already be in processing. Email us at <a href="mailto:hello@creativesolace.com">hello@creativesolace.com</a> as quickly as possible if you need to make a change.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>What if I entered the wrong shipping address?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@creativesolace.com">hello@creativesolace.com</a> within 24 hours of placing your order. If your package has already been shipped, we are not able to redirect it.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>My order arrived damaged. What do I do?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Take a photo of the damage and email it to <a href="mailto:hello@creativesolace.com">hello@creativesolace.com</a> within 72 hours of delivery. Include your order number. We will arrange a replacement or refund at no cost to you.</p>
        <p>Note: minor dents to the outer box that do not affect the product inside do not qualify for replacement.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Can I return my kit?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Yes. Under EU consumer law you have the right to return your purchase within 14 days of delivery, without giving a reason. The kit must be unused and in its original packaging with the B7000 seal intact. Return shipping costs are your responsibility.</p>
        <p>Email <a href="mailto:hello@creativesolace.com">hello@creativesolace.com</a> with your order number to start a return. See our <a href="/shipping">Shipping and Returns page</a> for full details.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-group">
    <h2 class="faq-section-title">Workshops and Events</h2>

    <details>
      <summary>Do I need experience to join a workshop?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>None at all. Our workshops are designed for people who have never painted or bedazzled before. We guide you through everything step by step.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>How do I book a workshop?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Click the Book a Workshop button on our website and fill in the short form. We will get back to you within 24 hours to confirm availability and details.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Can I book a private workshop for my group?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Yes. We specialise in private events for birthdays, bachelorette parties, and corporate team sessions. Fill in the quote form or email us at <a href="mailto:hello@creativesolace.com">hello@creativesolace.com</a> and we will put together a custom package.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Where do workshops take place?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>We can come to your home, your venue, or a location of your choice anywhere in the Netherlands. For some open public workshops we host at our own venue. The exact location is always confirmed when you book.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>How many people can join a workshop?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Paint and Sip: 6 to 25 people. Bedazzle and Sip: 6 to 20 people. Private events and corporate sessions can be customised based on your group size. Contact us for larger groups.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>I bought a ticket for an event. Where do I find it?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Your ticket is sent to your email address immediately after purchase. It includes a unique code and a QR code. Bring it on your phone or print it out. We scan it at the door.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Are workshop tickets refundable?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Workshop and event tickets are non-refundable once purchased, unless the event is cancelled by Creative Solace. If we cancel, you will receive a full refund within 14 days.</p>
        <p>If you booked via our quote form and can no longer attend, email us as soon as possible and we will do our best to find an alternative date.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-contact-strip">
    <p>Still have a question? We are happy to help.</p>
    <a href="mailto:hello@creativesolace.com" class="btn-primary">Email us at hello@creativesolace.com</a>
  </div>

</div>

